<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Grin" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Grin,</orth> to withdraw the lips from the teeth, to twist up and distort the features so as to betray malice, or scorn, or anguish: <bibl n="shak. ven 459" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 459</bibl>; cf. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 18</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.163" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 163</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 3, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 3, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 212</bibl> (Ff. <emph>jeering</emph>). <bibl n="shak. cym 5.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 3, 38</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>